'''Trisha Biggar''' is a costume designer who led the costume design departments for all three ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[prequel trilogy]] films, including the lavish [[Padmé Amidala's wardrobe|wardrobe]] of [[Monarch of Naboo|Queen]]-turned-[[Senator]] [[Padmé Amidala]], [[Jedi apparel|Jedi robes]], [[Boba Fett's armor|Jango Fett's armor]], [[Beru Whitesun Lars|Beru Whitesun]] and [[Owen Lars]], and the [[Tusken Raider]]s for [[2002]]'s [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']], which Biggar considers her most challenging project.<ref name="Clones at 20">{{SW|url=news/clones-at-20-trisha-biggar-interview|text=''Clones'' at 20 &#124; Costume Designer Trisha Biggar Reflects on Her Most Challenging Film}}</ref>

